    • Field Detail

      • ON_STARTUP_REQUEST

        public static final LifecycleEventType ON_STARTUP_REQUEST
        Notifies the serer startup request. This is different from LifecycleEventType.BEFORE_START, where this notifies the users request to start the server.

      • ON_RESTART_REQUEST

        public static final LifecycleEventType ON_RESTART_REQUEST
        Notifies the server restart request that is made via one of the management mechanisms of the UltraESB including raw JMX, UConsole and UTerm.

      • ON_SHUTDOWN_REQUEST

        public static final LifecycleEventType ON_SHUTDOWN_REQUEST
        Notifies the server shutdown request that is made via one of the management mechanisms of the UltraESB including raw JMX, UConsole and UTerm or a interruption via CTRL+C.

      • ON_SERVER_READY

        public static final LifecycleEventType ON_SERVER_READY
        Notifies for the server ready, once all actions are done in the startup process and the server is ready for accepting messages. This is identical to having a AFTER_LISTENING event, however since the name sounds wired the event is named as ON_SERVER_READY

      • ON_SERVER_REFRESH

        public static final LifecycleEventType ON_SERVER_REFRESH
        Notifies the server refresh event that can be triggered via one of the management mechanisms of the UltraESB including raw JMX, UConsole and UTerm

      • BEFORE_START

        public static final LifecycleEventType BEFORE_START
        Notifies before invoking the start operation of the server manager
